st acknowledgment we received from them. Future federation will enable cross-stack last-known-state status with non-Criome providers. *replication*|] High Minimum Zero [criome last-known-acknowledgment quorum-of-agreement federation replication])) (2alg ([(Technology (Software Distributed))] Decision [|The lojix deploy daemon serves connections concurrently (bounded by a permit cap), never blocking on in-progress nix builds; deploy state is per-request (each connection owns its pipeline cursor), the durable Store is the shared point locked briefly per sema op, and long nix effects hold no global lock.|] High Minimum Zero [lojix deploy-daemon nix sema concurrency])) (07pn ([(Technology (Software Distributed))] Decision [Every message carries an ORIGIN ROUTE as automatic metadata that is NOT declared in the schema - it is implicit on every message - acting as a return address that travels the whole way through signal then nexus then sema and back, so a reply is associated with the originating query when it returns. The origin route is internal to each component, a short statistically-unique identifier with effectively no clashes; it need not be a long hash, it is just a return address echoed back. Refines the message-identity intent records 930 960 by making the correlation identity an implicit round-trip return-address metadata field rather than a schema-declared field. *remote procedure call*] Medium VeryHigh Zero [origin-route signal nexus sema remote-procedure-call])) (3got ([(Technology (Software Distributed))] Decision [|Communicate is the wire trait between any two components, over binary rkyv with signal-frame (connection setup, async unique IDs for request-reply correlation, handshake). A universal mail-queue manager commits intent on accept; the reply carries a database marker (hash plus counter) so clients verify the transaction and guarantee local-state consistency against the daemon's authoritative database.|] Medium High Zero [communicate rkyv signal-fra